caption: Amazing new Albany Park business. Everything I have tried is delicious. Please stay in our neighborhood forever!

Dulce de Leche Café is an incredible addition to Albany Park! We tried their bagel lox and café de olla. The bagel lox was so filling, I loved the addition of avocado. The café de olla was some of the best I’ve ever had! It was so flavorful without being too sweet. The service was warm and friendly; all employees were wearing masks and there was hand sanitizer by the door. Their menu had so many delicious sounding options, it’s definitely worth a visit here. Can’t wait to come back to try more!
Sweet cafe! Awesome local spot with plenty of options both food and pastries. Staff and owner are great people. Keep up the great job.
Best place for sandwiches and cafe and everything's my favorites are the bagel lox of salmon and the my favorite sandwich the bread pudding its a must try
The carnitas is to die for, so are the black beans. They have dark matter coffee which is another perk. Incredibly kind and hospitable staff.
Food is great
Great space nice staff very friendly and good menu tasty crepe and drinks
We kept getting comments about how amazing the food was! Bar tenders were attentive and pour great drinks, all in all we have a great time! I would highly recommended this spot for any event.
We ordered crepes and chilaquiles verdes and latte's. Everything was delicious, my kids really enjoy the crepes and have been craving more! We be ordering again soon 😀
The food and lattes were amazing!
(Translated by Google) All delicious ... very nice place  (Original) Todo delicioso... muy bonito lugar
Delicious lavender latte and great atmosphere ❤️🥰

I had an amazing experience going to Dulce De Leche Cafe for the first time. I had the dulce de leche iced latte that was super good, as well as the lechera crepe that was amazing. The best part of my experience was the customer service that was provided by Omar who was the nicest person I have encountered in the last months. He noticed that I had my dog with me outside and even gave me a pupacchino, which made my  dog very happy. Thank you for such an amazing experience and I will be a returning customer. :D
Good cappuccino. Excellent service.

I just had they're carnitas torta. Phenomenal. This is not your standard Albany Park taco joint; they are playing in a different league. I cannot wait to try every single item on their menu. I'm so happy to have them in this neighborhood.

Such a cute, hidden gem in Albany Park! I have been meaning to try this café for a while now and I'm a little upset I didn't come in earlier. Their breakfast sandwiches are incredibly delicious. So far, I've had both the breakfast sandwich and the chorizo wrap/burrito. Absolutely mouth watering!  Their drink menu seems unlimited, varying from lattes, macchiatos, cappuccinos, and so forth.. I have only had their Rishi Teas (specifically the Guayusa Cacao), which let me tell you, I have been OBSESSING over all thanks to Omar's recommendation!  Most importantly, their customer service has been impeccable. Omar has been incredible since the first day I walked in. He is such a pleasure to talk to and has made each experience a delight. All of his recommendations have been spot on and if you're reluctant or unsure of what you want, he is more than happy to help you.  All in all, Dulce de Leche is 100% recommended. If I could give it 11/10 stars I would! Support your local, small family businesses!
First time visiting this gem. One of the best spots in the neighborhood. I will definitely be a regular. Food is amazing! Horchata latte is off the chain. The brother who run the place are awesome.
Best Latte and breakfast sandwich I’ve ever had!! Will definitely be back!
Love this place! My absolute favorite!!! Coffee and food are amazing and so is the service
Everything is delicious 😋!! Highly recommended 👌
The best place for coffee and bagels!
Love this place and their staff.
Everything in this place is amazing!

This place is the bomb! From service, through presentation and finally taste! Wow! Increíble! I’m demasiado picky but this place is so good que no tengo quejas solo elogios. The green chilaguiles son fuego en mi paladar. De verdad, tienen que probarlo. You will not be disappointed. The coffee is also amazing and will be tailored made how you like it. Es una delicia!

This spot opened up earlier this year mid pandemic and deserves all the love from Albany Park and it's neighbors! The food is fresh, and absolutely tasty, and the same can be said about their coffee! The drip is fresh, clean, and smooth, and all of their specialty drinks we've tried are great and balanced in flavor!
All of the food I've tried here from their breakfast sandwich, torta agoha and chilaquilies have been tasty and of high quality. Their coffees are also great.
The people here are so friendly and the Dulce de Leche latte is delicious and the food is all good and super fresh. I love this place.

Welcome to the neighborhood! This place is a real gem. The signature dulce de leche latte was delicious. I also ordered the beet salad and it was so refreshing and healthy. I can't wait to come back and try out some other options.

This new addition of Dulce to our neighborhood is so exciting!! Yesterday was my second time ordering from them and it was again, outstanding. First time we ate inside when restaurants were still open and we had the pleasure of chatting with the owner Omar and learned they had opened during covid times which breaks my heart but also know they are going to do amazing things. Being a chef myself, i know the importance and balance of a place that serves delicious food, knowledge of their menu, great staff and all around wonderful atmosphere. Second time was just yesterday when we ordered breakfast sandwiches, coffee and donuts for pick up. This place is must on your list to check out !!! I know i will be frequently ordering from them to show suppport!!!
Delicious high quality food made to order. I had the beet salad and grilled cheese with tomato. So delicious. Great service.

Dulce De Leche Cafe is amazing, everything is homemade and tastes delicious! Everything I ordered was delicious, the vibe and atmosphere makes this place so warm and inviting. I must say “Torta Ahogada and My Favorite Sandwich” are my favorite. Everything is homemade, which makes Dulce De Leche Cafe unique. Crepes are amazing, my daughter is in love with their crepes!  The staff is very friendly, knowledgeable and educated about their fresh quality items on the menu. They even have specials over the weekend, which are to die for. Lattes are right to the point, not overly sweet and have a great balance of flavor and a good kick of caffeine. Super friendly, very clean and great environment, I can’t wait to come back!

Top notch customer service paired with truly delicious food and coffee! This is a hidden gem in Mayfair that I am so happy to have stumbled upon. Both gentleman behind the counter were extremely knowledgeable and patient with my many questions. However, food is a star of its own and the crepes are not to be missed!! The chef came out to touch the table, providing a fine dining feel in a cozy cafe. We found out its a family ran restaurants, which during these uncertain times can't be easy. I know I will be ordering takeout to help support the little man, and can't wait to dine in again once restrictions lift!
Food is delicious 😋

Finally had to chance to try them. We got and egg and cheese breakfast sandwich, the torta ahogada and the chilaquiles. Everything was delicious and the owner is so nice and welcoming. Our dulce de leche coffee and chai latte were delicious! We'll be back for sure.

I'm in the U.S Army visiting my parents in Chicago and my mom brought me here to eat. Jeeezuz everyone who works there is nice. Thank you. Every single thing I ordered was amazing. It's legit a 10/10. I'll be back for sure
Great service and even better food. Torta Ahogada is delish...new favorite breakfast  restaurant!!! 😋 😍 🤗
Love the homemade bagels, the breakfast sandwich, and the coffee is amazing. I indulged today with an iced vanilla latte 🤤 so good!!!
Omg! This place is so amazing. The vibe and the atmosphere is so chill. I had a mocha latte, great! Roasted veggie bowl, amazing. I will definitely come here again. A true gem in Albany park.
This is my go-to place for coffee. Staff is always so welcoming and the coffee is so good!

Omar took INCREDIBLE care of us as my husband, best friend and I ran in right before closing (we were desperate for caffeine!) He educated us on the house favorites and even treated us to a free cup. The vibe of this place makes you feel like you’re a part of their family & the QUALITY is 11/10. Best latte I’ve ever had (Dulce de Leche)!!
Great cafe. Friendly staff and peaceful environment. Iced Horchata latte was delicious. 10/10 cafe. Would recommend.
The best lattes and the best breakfast sandwiches. Super friendly and great environment. Highly recommend
Best place in the neighborhood
Found this hidden gem on google and drove an hour to get here! Totally worth the drive, great food, really nice owners.

(Translated by Google) Super tasty and delicious !!! ☕😋 The flavor is delicious 👍  (Original) Super tasty and delicious!!! ☕😋 El sabor esta riquisimo 👍

Heard all the hype around this place for a long time now, and I finally had a chance to try it out and it definitely lives up to it. Had the My Favorite Sandwich which is a honey orange chicken on a brioche bun, and it was a wonderful mix of flavor. Can’t wait to try them out again.

One of the best flavored lattes in the area. We had the cocunut and the pumpkin spice lattes, and they did not disappoint. I had the green chilaquiles. They made them with a little crunch and added chile de árbol for some extra heat :) As for their crapes, I've had pretty much every single one on the menu and each one has it's own delicious flavor. My favorite the mazapán and nutella (w strawberries and bananas). They also have lighter food options and freshly made juices. Prices are reasonable and staff is always ready for any foodie questions.
Huge fan of this place. Delicious coffee and food. Staff is wonderful!
This place is the bomb! Their food and drinks are amazing!! They have me keep coming back!!
Too noisy everyday everytime. Puts too loud music. Need to respect neighbors

This hidden gem is a MUST visit , following COVID-19 guidelines the restaurant was clean with workers continuously disinfecting and hand sanitizer everywhere. Now as for the food I was surprised, the food was fantastic and authentic full of flavor with a modern twist. I ordered the torta, the burger and the pozole and not only  was it bursting with flavor but the quantity on our plates was more than enough. You definitely get a bang for your buck. The staff was friendly and kind giving the restaurant a welcoming ambient, the food wasn’t greasy and the ingredients were fresh and many of them imported which gave the food and outstanding quality. As for the lattes they seem to know what they’re doing, they were fresh, not overly sweet and with the perfect kick to give anyone a good wake up. This little gem should be on everybody’s “must visit” list! Will definitely be coming again for the food and drinks !
Their lattes are delicious! Their cucumber pineapple chia drink is also a must try.

Absolutely shocked to find such a fine cafe near Albany Park. Came back to visit my old stomping grounds and loved this place. Great music, food and the best customer service. Sat there for a couple hrs to telework while enjoying delicious mocha cafe. On point!!!!!
Great Customers Service, Great Coffee, Great Food, Great Prices! What more could you ask for? And conveniently close to transit
Amazing food, very clean and friendly service! So happy to have them in the neighborhood. Definitely my favorite place for a delicious meal and coffee!
Good food good service.a bit pricey  but overall  good
Horchata coffee, mazpan crepes, and torta hogada was solid.
Very nice, very clean! Great coffee, and really good food! This is exactly what the neighborhood  needed!
Very friendly service and the horchata latte is amazing!
Horchata latte is a must

Came here this morning after seeing a heavily positive post on Nextdoor about it and it is THAT good!  I drink a lot of chai and they have one of the good ones, Rishi. They also use abuelita chocolate in their choco-latte, which is an absolute game changer and hard to find in most cafes.  Those things alone were gonna keep me coming back but then hubby and I had their food. It is so delicious! I had the breakfast sandwich and he had today's special, Jerry's Chilaquiles, with chicken. Both were incredibly good and very satisfying. Definitely not your average cafe egg sandwich, I'll tell you that much. No, it's way better!  Come try them! Very friendly and sweet staff too. ❤️

I order here from Grubhub a couple times a week, and more if I can manage it. I just recently moved here and this lovely cafe has already become a big staple in my life. I'm slowly working my way through the menu, and so far I've enjoyed literally everything I've had. Their food is obviously made with love and every bite is delicious!
Great little spot. Food is awesome. Almost everything seems home made. Definitly reccomend a visit.
Great food great drinks
Great food and coffee, love the Iced Horchata. Friendly staff and cute cafe. Breakfast Banana Split was also amazing.

the staff here is very friendly and welcoming, the coffee is incredibly done, and the food is creative and beautifully served -- what's not to love? an excellent local cafe, making Albany Park proud :)
This place is completely amazing !  Love it will be a loyal customer for sure !
Amazing food. Great coffee, even by 3rd wave speciality coffee standards
Amazing hidden gem. We had the chilaquiles, breakfast sandwich, and My Favorite — all spectacular. And the oat milk latte was very good! Definitely will be coming back.
Great fresh food. Little wait but it is so worth it. Their coffee is awesome!

Saw the hype on a neighborhood FB page and decided to stop by and it earned all that hype. Horchata latte with oat milk is the sweetest, creamiest treat I’ve had in AP. And the My Favorite Sandwich had a lot more flavor than I expected, would order again. Staff is super friendly too! Definitely a hidden new gem.
We got the dulce de leche and horchata lattes.  Both were delicious.  Quick service.  Definitely recommend it.
Delicious food and coffee

When I tell you this place is a gem I mean it! I decided to try it out after seeing all the reviews and love it! I got the bagel lox and it’s soooo good, The ingredients chosen go together perfectly! so delicious. I also got an iced dulce de leche and it’s so yummy! I will definitely be coming here again, don’t think twice about trying it, just do it! I doubt there is anything like this around here. Oh and did I mention all the ingredientes are fresh! They also make their own bread!

Been here twice since they opened - once for coffee and once for sandwiches. The iced Choco latte was delicious. The bagel was nice and fresh, and the torta with carnitas was incredible.

Amazing sandwiches and excellent coffee. The crêpes are good, too, though I don't have much of a sweet tooth. That torta with carnitas is out of this world.

Got the bagel and lox sandwich and an iced coffee. This place rules!! I didn't have a breakfast bagel sandwich spot in the neighborhood until now. Friendly staff, chic environment, and dark matter coffee. Will be frequenting this spot mid and post rona ;)
Lovely staff and great bagels
Food and service is amazing! Would definitely recommend their horchata latté!!

Perfect! I ordered the "my favorite" chicken sandwich, a roasted veggie bowl, and mazpan crepe. The sandwich was delicious, with a real cut of chicken with a perfect combo of veggies. The veggie bowl had more veggies than I eat in a week, and the crepe was a fantastic dessert after. Everything was fresh and the greens were crisp and served with a smile👌.
My favorite chicken sandwich is AMAZING!!!.. so tasty perfect combinations. Also quick service.

Wow. I live just around the corner and my wallet is in trouble. I went in today for the second time and ordered a 12 oz. Dulce de leche and their sausage bacon egg and cheese sandwich on croissant and they both were delicious. That breakfast sandwich is no joke, they do not skimp out on anything plenty off all of those ingredients. It was honestly more like a burger than breakfast sandwich. They also serve Dark Matter coffee which is some of the best around Chicago. I’ll be back soon!

I really enjoy the freshness of their bread! Lattes on point! Enjoy the original Horchata Latte or Dulce de Leche Latte. Crepes, deligthfull, from a very simple Canelita to a more complex "La Sabrosa" with marscapone cheese.

What a wonderful surprise. This place is delicious. The dulce de leche crepe was phenomenal; we got it with strawberries- just amazing. The breakfast sandwich was great and the lox bagel was hearty and delicious.
Delicious crepes !! Great people ! Great service ! Clean place ! I would definitely come in every morning for a hot delicious coffee !!
They have really great food, I really recommend it! Their food is amazing and really delicious! Small & cute cafe.
Very delicious. I'm such a coffee person but WAY BETTER THAN STARBUCKS
Amazing food, amazing people.. very delicious meals and the coffee is the best!

Dulce De Leche should be on your "must visit" list asap. Everything, I mean everything is home made, even the bagels are made in house!  Very creative menu items with unique twists on old favorites.  I had the home made bagel, lox & cream cheese, packed with flavor and generously portioned, it's delicious and not something you're likely to soon forget.  Their "Turn me Nuts" dessert has to be seen to be believed and don't get me started with the "My Favorite" chicken sandwich, incredible.
Great customer service but most important delicious food.
